OL,3,CMines Advisory Group gets more
OL,4,Cgovernment cash to help war-torn
OL,5,Ccommunities
OL,7,FThe Manchester-based Mines Advisory
OL,8,FGroup (MAG) will receive an extra #17m
OL,9,Fof UK government cash to help war-torn
OL,10,Fcommunities across the world.
OL,12,FIt comes as the humanitarian group
OL,13,Fcontinues to help diffuse deadly
OL,14,Fexplosive devices in Ukraine, after
OL,15,Fmore than two years of conflict with
OL,16,FRussia.
OL,18,FAid worker Jon Cunliffe, from Bury,
OL,19,Fsays he's proud he can help farmers in
OL,20,Fwar-torn Ukraine clear their land of
OL,21,Fdeadly landmines.
