OL,7,F"The pressure to get that land back
OL,8,Finto productive use is not just from
OL,9,FUkrainian farmers and its government,
OL,10,Fbut from the international community
OL,11,Fas well. I am proud our demining work
OL,12,Fcan make such a difference."
OL,14,FUkraine has long been a top grain
OL,15,Fexporter, so the fact roughly 156,000
OL,16,Fsq km of agricultural land has been
OL,17,Frendered too dangerous to farm, means
OL,18,FRussia's invasion has had global
OL,19,Fconsequences, especially for food
OL,20,Finsecurity.
